entries.next: I really have nothing more for you to do. Please, I'd prefer to be alone just now.
entries.cantwork: Darling, are you currently occupied? Oh, I see you're busy. Do drop back here when you're free, hmm?
entries.npc_reset: How utterly tiresome. Very well, return to me when you may.
entries.npc_1_1: Darling! I absolutely insist you help me! I'm in the most awful jam over some forged records about my dearest Karrek. You know him, of course? Karrek Flim, the Corporate Sector Viceprex? Of course you know him. Will you bring me these forged records, taking whatever steps may be needed and not telling anyone? That would be lovely.
entries.npc_2_1: Too marvelous. Here are the coordinates where you'll find an aggravating data slicer named Bin Huusir or something like that. Do get the datadisc from him, and if violence is required, well, I suppose we'll all just have to live with that, hmm? Except Bin, of course.
entries.npc_3_1: You tiresome little being, leave me alone.
entries.npc_4_1: Well, if you know dear Karrek, you absolutely know he would in no way be responsible for ordering the leveling of numerous old-growth forests here in the Corellian system. You do understand that, don't you? Of course you do, any thinking being would. But that is what these detestable forged records are supposed to show. Will you get the data?
entries.npc_backtowork_1: Really, you know quite enough already. Please go, go, on your way!
entries.npc_reward_1: Darling! How pleasant. Here's a little something for your trouble. Ta.
entries.npc_work_1: Haven't you brought me that forged disc? Then why in the galaxy are you bothering me?
entries.npc_noloc_1: I have no clear idea where this data slicer is right now, but I expect one of Karrek's little people will tell me shortly. Talk to me again soon. Ta.
entries.npc_failure_1: Did you not bring that disc? Dear me, how tiresome you are. Ta.
entries.otherescort_1: I don't think I'm the one you're looking for.
entries.dontknowyou_1: I have no business with you.
entries.npc_breech_1: You're not hauling me back to that Corporate Sector dimwit!
entries.notit_1: I wanted the disc of Karrek Flim's correspondence. Don't you have it? How tiresome.
entries.player_reset_1: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.player_sorry_1: I'll keep working on the mission.
